-- Fairfield Energy May be Valued at $1.09 Billion in Initial Public Offering
-- Zijing Wu
-- 2010-07-05T08:09:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/fairfield-energy-may-be-valued-at-1-09-billion-in-initial-public-offering.html

          
          
             Fairfield Energy Plc, a North Sea oil
and gas company, may be valued at as much as 720 million pounds
($1.1 billion) in its initial public offering, according to a
term sheet for the sale.  
 Fairfield plans to sell as many as 150.4 million new shares
for 220 pence to 420 pence apiece, the document shows. The
company plans to raise about 330 million pounds in the IPO.  
 The shares are slated to start trading on July 15.  
